			<div id="post-139" class="hentry p1 post publish author-katt category-drawing tag-doodle tag-skerple y2010 m10 d01 h05">
    			<h1 class="entry-title">Skerple Friday: 20 Skerple Team Borax</h1>
<div class="entry-meta"><span class="author vcard">By <a class="url fn n" href="/author/admin/" title="View all posts by Katt">Katt</a></span><span class="meta-sep"> | </span><span class="entry-date"><abbr class="published" title="2010-10-01T09:00:15-0400">October 1, 2010</abbr></span></div><!-- .entry-meta -->
				<div class="entry-content">
<p>A hasty one because I seem to be running late and not really awake yet. I haven&#8217;t been drawing a ton lately because I just started knitting this great sweater, and I never get totally into knitting, so might as well ride the enthusiasm while I can.</p>
<p>They redesigned the Borax box. It used to be cheap-looking and awesome, and now it is all <a href="http://www.20muleteamlaundry.com/">dumb</a>. (I am too lazy to find a picture of the old box.) I figure if you&#8217;re going to redesign it, make it louder, make the word BORAX even bigger, and add lots of exclamation points. Right?</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/skerple-borax.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-140" title="skerple-borax" src="/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/skerple-borax.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="473" /></a></p>
<p>YEAH BORAX. Or how about add some cartoon endorsement and rhyming appeal in there?</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/skerple-zorakborax.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-141" title="skerple-zorakborax" src="/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/skerple-zorakborax.jpg" alt="" width="293" height="357" /></a></p>
<p>Zorak doesn&#8217;t look mean enough, but that&#8217;s because he&#8217;s excited to wash his sock.</p>
<p>Or: say it in Helvetica.</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/skerple-boraxhelv.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-142" title="skerple-boraxhelv" src="/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/skerple-boraxhelv.jpg" alt="" width="286" height="400" /></a></p>
<p>There&#8217;s this trend I&#8217;ve noticed where package designers who think they are TOTALLY BRILLIANT decide to just make the box entirely white and fill it with five-hundred-point Helvetica, line-breaking every two letters. Then they charge you extra for the Gutes Design.</p>
<p>That&#8217;s because they had to pay both the designer and the guy who told the designer they have to fix the space between the A and the X.</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/skerple-designdwarf.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-143" title="skerple-designdwarf" src="/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/skerple-designdwarf.jpg" alt="" width="419" height="468" /></a></p>

									</div>
